cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with sensor fusion for object detection using camera and lidar sensors. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is also likely as the paper discusses the application of the proposed method in robotics, specifically self-driving cars. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a novel method for sequential fusion using a semantic segmentation network. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper deals with the development of an AI-based system for object detection. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of semantic segmentation for object detection.
